### Fal Storage File Upload API (TypeScript)

Source: https://context7.com/fal-ai/fal-js/llms.txt

Demonstrates how to upload files to Fal's storage using the client library. Supports manual uploads, uploads with expiry configurations, and automatic file handling within requests. Files can be Blobs or File objects, and nested structures are also supported.

```typescript
import { fal } from "@fal-ai/client";

// Manual file upload
const file = new File(["image data"], "image.png", { type: "image/png" });
const uploadedUrl = await fal.storage.upload(file);
console.log("Uploaded to:", uploadedUrl);

// Upload with lifecycle configuration
const urlWithExpiry = await fal.storage.upload(file, {
  lifecycle: {
    expiresIn: "30d", // File expires in 30 days
  },
});

// Automatic file handling in requests - Blob/File objects are auto-uploaded
const result = await fal.run("fal-ai/imageutils/rembg", {
  input: {
    image: new File([imageBuffer], "photo.jpg", { type: "image/jpeg" }),
  },
});

// Works with any nested structure
const complexInput = await fal.storage.transformInput({
  images: [file1, file2],
  nested: {
    attachment: file3,
  },
});
// Returns same structure with files replaced by URLs
```

--------------------------------

### fal.storage - File Upload API

Source: https://context7.com/fal-ai/fal-js/llms.txt

Upload files to fal storage manually or automatically within request inputs.

```APIDOC
## POST /storage/upload

### Description
Uploads a file to fal storage. Files included in input objects are automatically uploaded during request execution.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
fal.storage.upload(file, options)

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **file** (File/Blob) - Required - The file object to upload.
- **options** (Object) - Optional - Configuration object including lifecycle settings (e.g., expiresIn).

### Request Example
const file = new File(["image data"], "image.png", { type: "image/png" });
const uploadedUrl = await fal.storage.upload(file, { lifecycle: { expiresIn: "30d" } });

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **url** (string) - The public URL of the uploaded file.
```

--------------------------------

### FalClient.subscribe

Source: https://github.com/fal-ai/fal-js/blob/main/docs/reference/interfaces/FalClient.html

Subscribes to a fal app endpoint execution, typically used for queue-based operations.

